◆ gen_resized_vect()

static OPERAND * gen_resized_vect ( OPERAND *  vop,
int  new_size,
int  start 
)
static

Create a new vector.

The new vactor will have the same type as vop with size new_size and filed with values from vop. This is useful for converting 3 element vectors to 4 element vectors and vice-versa.

Let's assume vop is a vector of 4 floats and new_size is 3. This will be expanded into following LLVM instruction:

%0 = shufflevector <4 x float> vop, <4 x float> undef,
          <3 x i32> <i32 0, i32 1, i32 2>

This will build a vector of 3 floats with 3 first elements from vop.

◆ match_types()

static MATCH_Kind match_types ( LL_Type *  ty1,
LL_Type *  ty2 
)
static

Does ty2 "match" ty1 or can ty2 be converted to ty1?

Parameters
ty1the result type
ty2a type

If ty1 is a ptr and ty2 is not, we have an error. In general, if the nesting level of ty1 is greater than that of ty2, then we have an error.

NB: The original algorithm did NOT enforce the latter condition above. The old algorithm would peel off all outer levels of array types blindly and until a non-array element type is found. This implied that this function would return MATCH_OK when the input types are i32 and [A x [B x [C x [D x i32]]]].
